{
  "stem": "11272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't think humans can ever, ever understand the suffering that we went through there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And this went on and on for about eight months till the Russians were coming close, and they started evacuating these camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I remember coming back-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] late that day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, let me go back a little bit.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The bombings were going on day after day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And, of course, we were praying and begging the Almighty, please have the bomb hit me already.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Take me out of my misery.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But yet you didn't want to give up on life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And one time, I remember, that it's broad daylight.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was about noon.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We didn't know whether it was Monday, Saturday, a holiday, or anything, because you had no comprehension what day it was or what-- what went on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And as the planes arrived, the German SS men all went into the shelters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we were there outside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And suddenly a boy run-- jumps, runs on top of a pile of dirt, and he starts praying.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It would happen to have been Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we were all around him and praying.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We had no siddur.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We had no mahzor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We had no prayer books.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But we prayed there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And the bombing lasted for about two, three hours.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And we managed to get some praying in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And after-- right after that, we were clearing out some of the rubbles after the bombing-- as a matter of fact, in the building that I worked in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And as I was pounding away-- I couldn't move the rubble.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And it turned out, when we cleared the way, it was a bomb.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And it was a long, long bomb.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "So they made us tie ropes around it.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
